cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

The paper deals with video predictive learning, which involves both computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a novel recurrent unit and a new architecture to address the vanishing gradient problem, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (AI) and neural networks (NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its model on both synthetic and real video datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (RO) category.
